JOHANNESBURG, October 8 – Two people have been killed after a light aircraft crashed into a house in Vorna Valley, Midrand, on Monday morning, a private ambulance service said. Netcare911 spokesperson Shawn Herbst said their paramedics responded at 11h20 to reports of a serious aircraft crash on Albertyn Road. “Reports from the scene indicate that a light aircraft came down into a residential garden. After a scene assessment the pilot and a gardener tragically died,” Herbst said. “All necessary authorities are on scene and have secured the area for a South African Civil Aircraft Aviation investigation.” (ANA)